'''Sivakumar Vijayan'''<ref name="auto">[[Satyajit Ray Film and Television Institute]]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tamilstudios.com/movie/2190|title=Vidiyum Munn (2013)|work=Tamilstudios - Review & Ratings}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moviecrow.com/movie/1504/vidiyum-munn-tamil-movie-review|title='Vidiyum Munn' Tamil Movie, Music Reviews ,Photos, Videos and News|author=Bharath Vijayakumar|date=29 November 2013|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barco.com/en/News/Press-releases/Tamil-thriller-Vidiyum-Munn-to-be-released-with-Auro-11-1-immersive-3D-audio.aspx|title=Tamil thriller Vidiyum Munn to be released with Auro 11-1 immersive 3D audio|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/vidiyum-munn-is-brilliant/20131130.htm|title=Vidiyum Munn is brilliant|date=30 November 2013|work=Rediff}}</ref>(born 17 May) is an [[India]]n [[Cinematographer]].<ref>[[:Category:Indian cinematographers]]</ref>

==Early life and education==
Sivakumar Vijayan<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theshoppingexpress.in/articles/issue-89-movie-review|title=TheShoppingExpress.in - Articles|work=The Shopping Express}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://clapsandboos.com/w/c/article/2003529b8b16a8bd67_74253874_01/vidiyum-munn-a-promising-movie-from-a-promising-team |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427200205/http://clapsandboos.com/w/c/article/2003529b8b16a8bd67_74253874_01/vidiyum-munn-a-promising-movie-from-a-promising-team |archivedate=27 April 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cinveda.com/talents/sivakumar-vijayan |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427182616/http://www.cinveda.com/talents/sivakumar-vijayan |archivedate=27 April 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2013/pooja-umashankar-challenged-malavika-125918.html|title=Pooja Umashankar Challenged By Malavika|work=www.filmibeat.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://moviebuff.com/sivakumar-vijayan|title=Sivakumar Vijayan on Moviebuff.com|work=Moviebuff.com}}</ref><ref name="unificationfrance.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.unificationfrance.com/spip.php?page=pages_mobiles&squelette_mobile=mobile/article&id_article=32590&lang=fr|title=Avant l'aube : La critique - Unification France|work=Unification France}}</ref> was born in [[Chennai]] to a middle-class Tamil family and grew up in Chennai and Kolkata. He is an electronics engineer from [[Madras University]] and pursued a master's in Media and Entertainment business administration. His passion for film photography started during his college days and after completing his engineering he joined [[Satyajit Ray Film and Television Institute]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cilect.org/groups/view/236 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140428022849/http://www.cilect.org/groups/view/236 |archivedate=28 April 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Kolkata specialising in Motion picture photography(cinematography). His first independent film as a cinematographer was [[Vidiyum Munn]] (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/articlelist/Vidiyum-Munn/movie-review/26593187.cms |title=Vidyum Munn movie review: Wallpaper, Story, Trailer at Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4345998/|title=Sivakumar Vijayan|work=IMDb}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-cinematographer/sivakumar-vijayan/sivakumar-vijayan-interview.html |title=Sivakumar Vijayan Interview |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tamilchannel.com/entertainment_page/9/6624/Vidiyum_Munn_Movie_Review_by_Common_Man/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-11-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131201015047/http://www.tamilchannel.com/entertainment_page/9/6624/Vidiyum_Munn_Movie_Review_by_Common_Man |archivedate=1 December 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pipinghotviews.com/moviereviews/tamil/vidiyum-munn-tamil-2013/|title=Vidiyum Munn (Tamil, 2013) - PipingHotViews|work=PipingHotViews}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://myoor.com/vidiyum-mun-2013-movie-review/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140428043135/http://myoor.com/vidiyum-mun-2013-movie-review/ |archivedate=28 April 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://lepakbro.blogspot.in/2014/01/vidiyum-munn-movie-review.html|title=Lepak Bro ! - Films Zone|publisher=}}</ref><ref>http://www.cinemanewstoday.com/vidiyum-munn-movie_review_with-a-social-message/</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindframes.com/vidiyum-munn-movie-review-2/|title=Vidiyum Munn Movie Review - Behind Frames|work=Behind Frames}}</ref>

==Career==
After graduating from [[Satyajit Ray Film and Television Institute]]<ref name="auto"/> (SRFTI), he assisted cinematographer [[P. C. Sreeram]] in the film [[Paa (film)]] (2009), [[Ishq (2012 film)]].He was also cinematographer for the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] feature film [[Vidiyum Munn]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3209556/|title=Vidiyum Munn (2013)|author=yashmishra91|date=29 November 2013|work=IMDb}}</ref> (2013)in which he was appreciated for the quality of photography and for the sense of framing by French critic Isabelle Arnaud.<ref name="unificationfrance.com"/> An article in [[The Hindu]] noted his work in [[vidiyum Munn]] for creating the mood,textures,disoriented canted angles and other factors in the film which affected the audience at an almost subconscious level.<ref>{{cite web|author=[[Baradwaj Rangan]] |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/vidiyum-munn-in-the-mood-for-thrills/article5408389.ece |title=Vidiyum Munn: In the mood for thrills |publisher=The Hindu |date= |accessdate=2013-11-30}}</ref> At present he is working on a sports drama [[Iruthi Sutru]] directed by sudha k prasad, the film is a bilingual made simultaneously in Tamil and as ''[[Irudhi Suttru|Saala Khadoos]]'' in Hindi. [[Irudhi Suttru|Saala Khadoos]] movie released in 2016 and became both critically acclaimed and box office hit. Even the film critic subash k jha appreciated his cinematography in Saala khadoos and mentioned him as the third hero of the film.<ref>[https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/saala-khadoos-review-madhavan-delivers-knockout-performance-in-an-ultimately-lightweight-film-2603040.html/amp]</ref> 2018-combo with director Selva ragavan

==Personal life==
He lives in [[Chennai]].

